post_text:
Job Opportunity!
The Jordan-Elbridge School District is looking to hire school bus drivers.
The job requires a valid NYS CDL class B with Passenger (P) and School Bus (S) endorsement motor vehicle license, but we will train you if you have the ability and means to obtain the license. All of our buses have an automatic transmission.
Must be 21 years of age to apply. A Contracted Driver’s salary is $24.92 per hour. Benefits include affordable health and dental insurance, and free vision insurance. A Substitute Driver’s salary is $18.25 per hour – but they do not receive benefits. To apply, please go to: http://www.jecsd.org/districtpage.cfm?pageid=1586

The Jordan Elbridge 2019 Field Band show titled Band 22 was in honor of the Navy Band Unit 22 stationed onboard the USS Arizona BB-39. post_text:
Here is the 2nd virtual ensemble recording for the Jordan-Elbridge Senior High Concert Band: Avengers: Endgame! This is the first half of this arrangement - the second half, along with more new music, will be coming out in the next few weeks. They performed this on their winter concert, and it was voted as the majority favorite to record for this project.

High school instrumental music teacher Zach Moser said, "It is an absolute joy to work with these students and to get some semblance of the rehearsal/performance process by helping them record their parts and then putting this all together. Things like this will never come anywhere close to the experience of being in the band room together, but it does allow us to still work as a team and as a band family to create something beautiful and awesome."

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eIT58kZzr94&feature=youtu.be&fbclid=IwAR3twqKcy9MYeAABANHLAhL7_L3-THNT6oXncnf7HPgfZVVUxIc0C6fmM8k

post_text:
Future SAT Administrations, Including September 26

The College Board is working to ensure that students will have opportunities to take the SAT to make up for this spring’s lost administrations. They've added a new SAT administration for Saturday, September 26, 2020. This date will be for the SAT only, in the United States and internationally, with no SAT Subject Tests available. Sunday testing for religious reasons will be on September 27.

post_text:
Congratulations to first grader Collin Campion, a student from Mrs. Goetz class, who was nominated by Elbridge Elementary resource officer McIlroy as an honorary junior deputy with the Cayuga County Sheriff’s Office.
McIlroy said that Collin was nominated because “Collin is a great kid who always tries to do the right thing while at school. He is very caring of other students and staff and is always smiling. Collin always talks to me about safety and reminds me that he is my partner.”

Cayuga County Sheriff Brian Schenck said the sheriff’s office was “recruiting” junior deputy sheriffs who live up to the mission of the office by enhancing the quality of life of others or helping to secure a safe community, while maintaining the trust and respect of those that know them.

Job Opportunity!
The Jordan-Elbridge School District is looking to hire full-time and substitute school bus drivers.
The job requires a valid NYS CDL class B with Passenger (P) and School Bus (S) endorsement motor vehicle license, but we will train you if you have the ability and means to obtain the license. All of our buses have an automatic transmission.
Must be 21 years of age to apply.
A contracted driver’s salary is $24.19 per hour. Benefits include affordable health and dental insurance, and free vision insurance. A substitute driver’s salary is $18.25 per hour – but they do not receive benefits. Click the link to apply
http://www.jecsd.org/districtpage.cfm?pageid=1586

post_text: Jordan-Elbridge students Zoe Magid, Leah Munson and Kylee Trexler recently competed in the Summit cheerleading competition on May 2-5, 2019 in Orlando with their team from the Syracuse gym, Core Athletix. On March 31, their team, "Black Ice" earned their bid while competing at Temple University. The team took home first place in their division along with earning the title of "Grand Champions" for having the highest score in the more-than-60-team competition. post_text: The Jordan-Elbridge School District is looking to hire three school bus drivers, one bus monitor and substitute monitors. The bus driver positions require a valid NYS CDL class B with Passenger (P) and School Bus (S) endorsement motor vehicle license, but we will train you if you have the ability and means to obtain the license. All of our buses have an automatic transmission. Must be 21 years of age to apply. A contracted driver’s salary is $23.49 per hour. Benefits include affordable health and dental insurance, and free vision insurance. A substitute driver’s salary is $18.25 per hour – but they do not receive benefits. Bus monitors must be at least 19 years old and able to work with all school-age children. They must also pass drug testing and be physically able to assist students off the bus in case of an emergency. A bus monitor’s pay is $16.68 per hour, and substitute monitors are paid $11.10 an hour. To apply, go to: http://www.jecsd.org/districtpage.cfm?pageid=1586
text: The Jordan-Elbridge School District is looking to hire three school bus drivers, one bus monitor and substitute monitors. The bus driver positions require a valid NYS CDL class B with Passenger (P) and School Bus (S) endorsement motor vehicle license, but we will train you if you have the ability and means to obtain the license. All of our buses have an automatic transmission. Must be 21 years of age to apply. A contracted driver’s salary is $23.49 per hour. Benefits include affordable health and dental insurance, and free vision insurance. A substitute driver’s salary is $18.25 per hour – but they do not receive benefits. Bus monitors must be at least 19 years old and able to work with all school-age children. They must also pass drug testing and be physically able to assist students off the bus in case of an emergency. A bus monitor’s pay is $16.68 per hour, and substitute monitors are paid $11.10 an hour. To apply, go to: http://www.jecsd.org/districtpage.cfm?pageid=1586
